file.name: openapi.yml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.1
info:
  x-ballerina-display:
    label: Shipwire Warehouse
    iconPath: "icon.png"
  title: Shipwire Warehouses API
  description: |
    This is a generated connector for [Shipwire Warehouses API v3.0](https://www.shipwire.com/developers/warehouse/) OpenAPI specification.
    The Warehouse API is used to manage Shipwire Anywhere warehouses and dropship locations. 
    Use it to create a new warehouse, to update an existing warehouse, or to get information about already created warehouses.
  x-ballerina-init-description: >
    The connector initialization requires setting the API credentials. 
  
    Create a [Shipwire account](https://www.shipwire.com) and obtain tokens by following [this guide](https://www.shipwire.com/developers/getting-started).
  version: "3.0"
servers:
- url: https://api.shipwire.com/
security:
- basicAuth: []
paths:
  /api/v3.1/warehouses:
    get:
      summary: Get warehouses
      description: Get a collection of warehouses
      operationId: getWarehouses
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: query
        description: Filter by warehouse ids, supports comma separated list
        schema:
          type: integer
      - name: externalId
        in: query
        description: Filter by warehouse external ids, supports comma separated list
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: name
        in: query
        description: Filter by warehouse names, supports comma separated list
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: vendorId
        in: query
        description: Filter by associated vendor's id, supports comma separated list
        schema:
          type: integer
      - name: vendorExternalId
        in: query
        description: Filter by associated vendor's external id, supports comma separated
          list
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: country
        in: query
        description: Filter by country, supports comma separated list
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: generatesLabels
        in: query
        description: Filter by warehouses that require label generation
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: type
        in: query
        description: Filter by type ("SHIPWIRE", "SHIPWIRE_ANYWHERE")
        schema:
          type: string
          enum:
          - SHIPWIRE
          - SHIPWIRE_ANYWHERE
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetWarehousesResponse'
    post:
      summary: Create a new warehouse
      description: Create a new warehouse
      operationId: postWarehouse
      requestBody:
        description: Create a new warehouse request
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/CreateANewWarehouseRequest'
        required: true
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/CreateANewWarehouseResponse'
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
  /api/v3.1/warehouses/{id}:
    get:
      summary: Get a warehouse
      description: Get a warehouse by id or external id.
      operationId: GetWarehousesById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The warehouse id or external id.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetAWarehouseResponse'
    put:
      summary: Update a warehouse
      description: Modify a warehouse based on its id or external id
      operationId: PutWarehousesById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The warehouse's id or external id.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      requestBody:
        description: Update a warehouse request
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/UpdateAWarehouseRequest'
        required: true
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Create a new warehouse response"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/CreateANewWarehouseResponse'
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
  /api/v3.1/warehouses/{id}/retire:
    post:
      summary: Retire a warehouse
      description: Indicates that the warehouse will not longer be used. If the warehouse
        is not associated with any active vendors or orders, the warehouse will be
        deleted. Otherwise the warehouse will have its "isActive" property set to
        false.
      operationId: PostWarehousesRetireById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: Warehouse id or external id
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Retire a warehouse response"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/RetireAWarehouseResponse'
        404:
          description: Unexpected error in API call. See HTTP response body for details.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/RetireAWarehouse404Response'
  /api/v3.1/warehouses/{id}/containers:
    get:
      summary: Get containers associated with a warehouse
      operationId: GetWarehousesContainersById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The warehouse id or external id.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Get containers associated with a warehouse response"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetContainersAssociatedWithAWarehouseResponse'
  /api/v3.1/warehouses/{id}/carriers:
    get:
      summary: Get carriers associated with a warehouse
      description: Returns a list of carriers associated with the specified warehouse.
      operationId: GetWarehousesCarriersById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The warehouse id or external id.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Get carriers response"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetCarriersResponse'
  /api/v3.1/warehouses/{id}/addCarriers:
    post:
      summary: Add carriers to a warehouse
      description: Creates the association of a carrier with the specified warehouse.
      operationId: AddCarriersByIdToWarehouse
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: Warehouse id or external id.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      requestBody:
        description: Add carrier request
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/AddCarrierRequest'
        required: true
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Get carriers response"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetCarriersResponse'
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
  /api/v3.1/warehouses/{id}/removeCarriers:
    post:
      summary: Remove carriers to a warehouse
      description: Removes the association of a carrier with the specified warehouse,
        and returns the list of updated carriers supported for the warehouse.
      operationId: RemoveCarriersByIdToWarehouse
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: Warehouse id or external id.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      requestBody:
        description: Remove carrier request
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/RemoveCarrierRequest'
        required: true
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Get carriers response"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetCarriersResponse'
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
components:
  schemas:
    WarehouseServerResponse:
      title: Warehouse Server Response
      type: object
      properties:
        status:
          type: integer
          description: This is the HTTP status code.
          example: 200
        message:
          type: string
          description: This is the HTTP status message.
          example: Successful
      description: Get Warehouses Response based on the criteria provided in the URL
    WarehouserPaginationResponse:
      title: Warehouse Pagination Response
      type: object
      properties:
        offset:
          type: integer
          description: This is an integer that matches the offset given in the request
            and dictates the number of items to skip while fetching results. For example,
            there is a preset limit of 20 results per page. If there are 30 total
            results and offset is set to 20, then the response will show the second
            "page" of results, with items 21 to 30.
          example: 0
        total:
          type: integer
          description: Total number of available items in the API response.
          example: 1
        previous:
          type: string
          description: A link used to fetch the previous set or page of items in the
            API response.
          example: null
        next:
          type: string
          description: A link used to fetch the next set or page of items in the API
            response.
          example: null
      description: Server Pagination Response
    GetWarehousesResponse:
      allOf:
      - $ref: '#/components/schemas/WarehouseServerResponse'
      - title: Get Warehouses Response
        type: object
      - type: object
        description: Get Warehouses Response based on the criteria provided in the
          URL
      - type: object
    GetCarriersResponse:
      allOf:
      - $ref: '#/components/schemas/WarehouseServerResponse'
      - title: Get Carriers Response
        type: object
      - type: object
        description: Get Carriers Response based on the criteria provided in the URL
      - type: object
    PostWarehouseRequest:
      title: Post request to create a new warehouse
      required:
      - address
      - isActive
      - labelFormat
      - name
      type: object
      properties:
        externalId:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: A unique user-provided identifier for the warehouse in an external
            system.
          example: "3"
        name:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: Name of the warehouse
          example: West Coast DC
        code:
          maxLength: 25
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the code assigned to the warehouse for easy reference.
          example: RCKTS
        vendorId:
          type: integer
          description: A unique ID assigned to each vendor in the Shipwire system.
            (See the Vendors API.)
        vendorExternalId:
          type: string
          description: A unique user provided identifier for a vendor in an external
            system.
          example: null
        isActive:
          type: integer
          description: A boolean which indicates whether or not the warehouse is available
            to the customer for storage, shipping and receiving inventory.
          example: 1
        address:
          description: Address
          type: object
        latitude:
          maximum: 9E+1
          minimum: -9E+1
          type: number
          description: Latitude of the warehouse. This is useful for routing purposes
            to find the nearest warehouse.
          format: float
          example: 37.7915
        longitude:
          maximum: 1.8E+2
          minimum: -1.8E+2
          type: number
          description: Longitude of the warehouse. This is useful for routing purposes
            to find the nearest warehouse.
          format: float
          example: -122.402
        isRoutable:
          type: integer
          description: A boolean which indicates whether orders may be routed to this
            warehouse by our routing engine.
          example: 1
        labelFormat:
          type: string
          description: This is the generic format of the label that the warehouse
            generates for each customer
          example: 8.5x11
          enum:
          - 4x6
          - 8.5x11
        generatesLabels:
          type: integer
          description: A boolean which indicates whether or not the warehouse can
            generate shipping labels. These labels are stored on the server and can
            be given to the customer if required
          example: 1
        returnWarehouseId:
          type: integer
          description: This is the unique ID of the Shipwire warehouse used for RMA
            process and will store returned goods.
          example: 11
        returnWarehouseExternalId:
          maxLength: 11
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the external ID of the Shipwire warehouse used for
            RMA process.
          example: null
      description: Sample Post request to create a new warehouse
    CreateANewWarehouseRequest:
      title: Create a New Warehouse Request
      description: Create a New Shipwire Anywhere Warehouse
      allOf:
      - $ref: '#/components/schemas/PostWarehouseRequest'
      - type: object
    CreateANewWarehouseResponse:
      allOf:
      - $ref: '#/components/schemas/WarehouseServerResponse'
      - title: Create a New Warehouse Response
        type: object
      - type: object
        description: Response for new Shipwire Anhywhere Warehouse creation
      - type: object
    GetAWarehouseResponse:
      allOf:
      - $ref: '#/components/schemas/WarehouseServerResponse'
      - title: Get a Warehouse Response
        type: object
      - type: object
        description: Get a Warehouse information for the mentioned ID
      - type: object
    UpdateAWarehouseRequest:
      title: Update a Warehouse Request
      type: object
      properties:
        externalId:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: A unique user-provided identifier for the warehouse in an external
            system.
          example: "3"
        name:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: Name of the warehouse
          example: West Coast DC
        code:
          maxLength: 25
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the code assigned to the warehouse for easy reference.
          example: RCKTS
        vendorId:
          type: integer
          description: A unique ID assigned to each vendor in the Shipwire system.
            (See the Vendors API.)
        vendorExternalId:
          type: string
          description: A unique user provided identifier for a vendor in an external
            system.
          example: null
        isActive:
          type: integer
          description: A boolean which indicates whether or not the warehouse is available
            to the customer for storage, shipping and receiving inventory.
          example: 1
        address:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/WarehouseAddress'
        latitude:
          maximum: 9E+1
          minimum: -9E+1
          type: number
          description: Latitude of the warehouse. This is useful for routing purposes
            to find the nearest warehouse.
          format: float
          example: 37.7915
        longitude:
          maximum: 1.8E+2
          minimum: -1.8E+2
          type: number
          description: Longitude of the warehouse. This is useful for routing purposes
            to find the nearest warehouse.
          format: float
          example: -122.402
        isRoutable:
          type: integer
          description: A boolean which indicates whether orders may be routed to this
            warehouse by our routing engine.
          example: 1
        generatesLabels:
          type: integer
          description: A boolean which indicates whether or not the warehouse can
            generate shipping labels. These labels are stored on the server and can
            be given to the customer if required
          example: 1
        returnWarehouseId:
          maxLength: 11
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the unique ID of the Shipwire warehouse used for RMA
            process and will store returned goods.
          example: "11"
        returnWarehouseExternalId:
          maxLength: 11
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the external ID of the Shipwire warehouse used for
            RMA process.
          example: null
      description: Update Shipwire Warehouse Information
    RetireAWarehouseResponse:
      title: Retire a Warehouse Response
      type: object
      properties:
        status:
          type: integer
          description: This is the HTTP status code.
          example: 200
        message:
          maxLength: 30
          minLength: 6
          type: string
          description: This is the HTTP status message.
          example: Deleted
        resourceLocation:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the linked resource.
            A "null" value would mean that no further information is available for
            that resource.
          example: null
      description: Delete Shipwire Anywhere Warehouse from the system
    RetireAWarehouse404Response:
      title: Retire a warehouse 404 response
      type: object
      properties:
        status:
          type: integer
          description: This is the HTTP status code.
          format: int32
          nullable: true
          example: 404
        message:
          type: string
          description: This is the HTTP status message.
          example: Warehouse not found
        resourceLocation:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the linked resource.
            A "null" value would mean that no further information is available for
            that resource.
          example: https://api.shipwire.com/api/v3.1/warehouses?offset=0&limit=1
    GetContainersAssociatedWithAWarehouseResponse:
      title: Get containers associated with a warehouse response
      type: object
      properties:
        status:
          type: integer
          description: This is the HTTP status code.
          example: 200
        message:
          type: string
          description: This is the HTTP status message.
          example: Successful
        resourceLocation:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the linked resource.
            A "null" value would mean that no further information is available for
            that resource.
          example: https://api.shipwire.com/api/v3.1/containers?offset=0&limit=20
        resource:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetContainersAssociatedWithAWarehouseResponse_resource'
      description: Get list of containers associated with Warehouse. This contains
        information for both Shipwire and Shipwire anywhere Warehouse
    WarehouseAddress:
      title: Warehouse Address
      required:
      - address1
      - city
      - country
      - name
      - phone
      - postalCode
      - state
      type: object
      properties:
        address1:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the first line of the address of the warehouse.
          example: 1409 S Lilac Ave
        address2:
          maxLength: 35
          minLength: 0
          type: string
          description: This is the second line of the address of the warehouse.
          example: ""
        address3:
          maxLength: 35
          minLength: 0
          type: string
          description: This is the third line of the address of the warehouse.
          example: ""
        city:
          maxLength: 35
          type: string
          description: City where the warehouse is located.
          example: Bloomington
        state:
          maxLength: 3
          minLength: 2
          type: string
          description: State where the warehouse is located.
          example: CA
        postalCode:
          maxLength: 10
          pattern: /^[0-9]{5}(?:-[0-9]{4})?$/
          type: string
          description: Postal code of the warehouse
          example: "92316"
        country:
          type: string
          description: 2 digit country code of the warehouse
          example: US
        continent:
          type: string
          description: Name of the continent where the warehouse is located.
          format: enum
          example: NORTH_AMERICA
          enum:
          - NORTH_AMERICA
          - SOUTH_AMERICA
          - EUROPE
          - AFRICA
          - ASIA
          - AUSTRALIA
          - ANTARCTICA
        name:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: Name of the warehouse
          example: NGL Bloomington
        email:
          type: string
          description: Email address of contact at the warehouse for any communication
          example: foo@bar.com
        phone:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: Contact phone number of the warehouse for any communication
          example: 650-561-4800
        fax:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: Contact fax number of the warehouse for any communication
          example: null
      description: Shipwire Anywhere Warehouse Address
    WarehouseInformation:
      title: Warehouse Information
      type: object
      properties:
        id:
          type: integer
          description: A unique auto-generated ID assigned to each new warehouse added
            to the Shipwire Platform.
          example: 11
        externalId:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: A unique user-provided identifier for the warehouse in an external
            system.
          example: "3"
        name:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: Name of the warehouse
          example: LA
        code:
          maxLength: 25
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the code assigned to the warehouse for easy reference.
          example: LAX3
        vendorId:
          type: integer
          description: A unique ID assigned to each vendor in the Shipwire system.
            (See the Vendors API.)
        vendorExternalId:
          type: string
          description: A unique user provided identifier for a vendor in an external
            system.
          example: null
        isActive:
          type: integer
          description: A boolean which indicates whether or not the warehouse is available
            to the customer for storage, shipping and receiving inventory.
          format: enum
          example: 1
        address:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/WarehouseInformation_address'
        latitude:
          maximum: 9E+1
          minimum: -9E+1
          type: number
          description: Latitude of the warehouse. This is useful for routing purposes
            to find the nearest warehouse.
          format: float
          example: 37.7915
        longitude:
          maximum: 1.8E+2
          minimum: -1.8E+2
          type: number
          description: Longitude of the warehouse. This is useful for routing purposes
            to find the nearest warehouse.
          format: float
          example: -122.402
        isRoutable:
          type: integer
          description: A boolean which indicates whether orders may be routed to this
            warehouse by our routing engine.
          format: enum
          example: 1
        generatesLabels:
          type: integer
          description: A boolean which indicates whether or not the warehouse can
            generate shipping labels. These labels are stored on the server and can
            be given to the customer if required
          format: enum
          example: 1
        type:
          type: string
          description: This is the type of the warehouse. It can be Shipwire or Shipwire
            Anywhere.
          format: enum
          example: SHIPWIRE
          enum:
          - SHIPWIRE
          - SHIPWIRE_ANYWHERE
        labelFormat:
          type: string
          description: This is the generic format of the label that the warehouse
            generates for each customer
          format: enum
          example: 8.5x11
          enum:
          - 4x6
          - 8.5x11
        combineShippingDocuments:
          type: boolean
          description: This warehouse property ensures all shipping labels generated
            are a combination of packing list and label.
          example: false
        returnWarehouseId:
          maxLength: 11
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the unique ID of the Shipwire warehouse used for RMA
            process and will store returned goods.
          example: "11"
        returnWarehouseExternalId:
          maxLength: 11
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the external ID of the Shipwire warehouse used for
            RMA process.
          example: null
        physicalWarehouseId:
          type: integer
          description: A shipwire warehouse ID used to identify a specific physical
            warehouse that corresponds to a Shipwire Anywhere warehouse and is useful
            in consolidating inventory. If the SKU item is at a Shipwire warehouse,
            then this will be "null".
          example: 5011
        containers:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/WarehouseInformation_containers'
        carriers:
          type: string
          description: These are customizations to carrier settings (ex. FDX 1D) specific
            to a warehouse. May relate to destination/origin country & zip code, max
            shipment dimensions & carrier capabilities etc.
          example: null
      description: Warehouse resource information
    CarrierResourceLocation:
      title: Carrier Resource Location
      type: object
      properties:
        resourceLocation:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the linked resource.
            A "null" value would mean that no further information is available for
            that resource.
          example: https://api.shipwire.com/api/v3.1/carriers/ABM-PLITE
        resource:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetCarrierProperties'
      description: Carrier Resource Location
    GetWarehouseResources:
      title: Warehouse Resources
      type: object
      properties:
        offset:
          type: integer
          description: This is an integer that matches the offset given in the request
            and dictates the number of items to skip while fetching results. For example,
            there is a preset limit of 20 results per page. If there are 30 total
            results and offset is set to 20, then the response will show the second
            "page" of results, with items 21 to 30.
          example: 0
        total:
          type: integer
          description: Total number of available items in the API response.
          example: 1
        previous:
          type: string
          description: A link used to fetch the previous set or page of items in the
            API response.
          example: null
        next:
          type: string
          description: A link used to fetch the next set or page of items in the API
            response.
          example: null
        items:
          description: GetWarehouseResources items
          type: array
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetWarehouseResources_items'
      description: Warehouse Resources
    CarrierResources:
      title: Carrier Resources
      type: object
      properties:
        offset:
          type: integer
          description: This is an integer that matches the offset given in the request
            and dictates the number of items to skip while fetching results. For example,
            there is a preset limit of 20 results per page. If there are 30 total
            results and offset is set to 20, then the response will show the second
            "page" of results, with items 21 to 30.
          example: 0
        total:
          type: integer
          description: Total number of available items in the API response.
          example: 1
        previous:
          type: string
          description: A link used to fetch the previous set or page of items in the
            API response.
          example: null
        next:
          type: string
          description: A link used to fetch the next set or page of items in the API
            response.
          example: null
        items:
          description: Items
          type: array
          items:
            type: object
            properties: {}
      description: Carrier Resources
    ContainerDimensions:
      title: Container Dimensions
      type: object
      properties:
        length:
          maximum: 108
          minimum: 0.1
          type: number
          description: This is the length of the container based on its Unit of Measurement
            (lengthUnit)
          format: float
          example: 5.0
        width:
          maximum: 108
          minimum: 0.1
          type: number
          description: This is the width of the container based on its Unit of Measurement
            (widthUnit)
          format: float
          example: 5.0
        height:
          maximum: 108
          minimum: 0.1
          type: number
          description: This is the width of the container based on its Unit of Measurement
            (widthUnit)
          format: float
          example: 1.0
        weight:
          maximum: 108
          minimum: 0.1
          type: number
          description: This is the weight of the container based on its Unit of Measurement
            (weightUnit)
          format: float
          example: 0.0
        maxWeight:
          maximum: 108
          minimum: 0.1
          type: number
          description: This is the maximum weight that the container can hold based
            on its Unit of Measurement (maxWeightUnit)
          format: float
          example: 150.0
        lengthUnit:
          type: string

            container.
          example: USD
